---
---
<section
  data-test="how-it-works"
  class="py-16 px-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto"
>
  <div class="border-t pt-16" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">
    <h2 class="font-sans text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wider mb-10" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">
      How It Works
    </h2>

    <p class="font-serif text-lg mb-10 max-w-2xl" style="color: var(--color-text);">
      Four commands drive the entire workflow, in order. Each hands off to the next.
      The spec is the source of truth throughout.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      {[
        {
          cmd: '/rs-init',
          title: 'Initialize',
          desc: 'Scaffold the RootSpec directory structure and configure your project. Sets up the five-level hierarchy and convention files.',
          io: 'Input: empty directory → Output: scaffold + configuration',
        },
        {
          cmd: '/rs-spec',
          title: 'Specify',
          desc: 'AI-driven interview that extracts your product\'s philosophy, truths, and interactions. Produces a validated, executable specification across all five levels.',
          io: 'Input: product idea / seed → Output: validated spec',
        },
        {
          cmd: '/rs-impl',
          title: 'Implement',
          desc: 'AI agents implement features from the validated user stories, one story at a time. Each story is tested before the next begins. Stops when all stories pass.',
          io: 'Input: validated spec → Output: working code + tests',
        },
        {
          cmd: '/rs-validate',
          title: 'Validate',
          desc: 'Continuous validation gate. Runs all user stories against the current implementation. Generates a compliance report. Catches drift before it compounds.',
          io: 'Input: spec + code → Output: validation report',
        },
      ].map(({ cmd, title, desc, io }) => (
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 pt-1">
            <code
              class="font-mono text-sm px-2 py-1 rounded"
              style="background-color: var(--color-code-bg); color: var(--color-accent); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); white-space: nowrap;"
            >
              {cmd}
            </code>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-sans text-base font-medium mb-1" style="color: var(--color-text);">{title}</h3>
            <p class="font-serif text-sm leading-relaxed mb-1" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">{desc}</p>
            <p class="font-mono text-xs" style="color: var(--color-text-muted); opacity: 0.7;">{io}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
